Covariant return types :
Return type of the overridden method in the child can be of 
the same as Parents return type or a covariant return type. 

Covariant return types: The child class of the parents return type. 
Eg: If BankAccount is a parent class and SavingsAccount is the child class
    If BankAccount has a method with BankAccount object as a return type.
    then in the child class this method can be overridden
    with:
    a. same BankAccount object as return type OR
    b. return type can be the subclass of BankAccount i.e SavingsAccount.

    
   
   
   
   
   Object Casting: 
   Converting one type of object into another type of object is known as 
   Casting.
   
   When an object reference  refers to a Child class object, it is known as 
   Upcasting. 
   
   eg: Parent obj = new Child(); //upcasting
   
   
   Upasting automatically. 
   It happens implicitly. 
   
   
   Downcasting: Converting Parent reference to a Child referece.
   
   eg: Parent p = new Child();//upcasting or automatic casting
       Child c = (Child)p;// down casting
   
   
   
   
   
   
   